WorkItem.Description:
Somehow broke my character file.  Note the weirdness with the boots in the comparison pane.  If this shows up normal to others, I will simply build a new local version of the program and move on my life.  ;)
 
The events preceding this were the addition of new pants and a ranged weapon, two subsequent Optimize routines, and a single run of the Build Upgrade.
 
This does not happen with other character files, and does not seem to be a talent/options issue.

Comments.Message:
Update : After noticing some DPSWarr updates from today, I went ahead and rebuilt Rawr.  Upon attempting to load the same "AeroDeeps Live - Arms" character profile, I encountered an error.  I ignored it to see the functionality, and it failed to load the character after 5 minutes.  the "Load Character progress box" become unresponsive.  This occurred upon opening /any/ previously saved file, if I did not switch the module it was working on (for example, attempting to load a Boomkin, when the DPSWarr module was the latest module to be opened previously).  I am able to load a character from the armory successfully that defaults Rawr the DPSWarr module.

Oh.  And, I had originally thought that this was related to the previous error, though I am not 100% sure of this.

Guys,
Create a new blank DPSWarr character and save the file, open the .xml and compare the long list of true/falses between the two. The new character will have a longer list, copy it over and you can then open the old file. You may need to reselect some of the abilities to have it the way you had it.

The problem is when I add new functionality, some things don't translate from old files to new but you can manually fix them.

As far as other characters not loading as well, open those files and remove all the settings that had to do with DPSWarr, a single XML can end up with the save info for every model that is loaded (intentionally or otherwise) while that xml is active in Rawr.

After fixing the file as instructed, I am running into a weird error.  If I remove my helm, I get the error as shown below (first error, before the Loaded Assemblies list).  Similarly, if I remove my pants and/or chest, and then try to click on the item slot, I get what I believe to be a related error (second error, before the LA list).

This almost seems to be an issue with special gems in that the chest and the legs contain Dragon's Eyes, and the head could be explained to a Stormjewel or a meta, but then, the neck (which contains my third Dragon's Eye) does not initiate this error.

The item number referenced in the error is the design for a level seventy trinket Rogue trinket.

Attaching new character file.

Please tell me I'm just an idiot, and am missing something obvious here.
